EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cSetAttribute
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Set Attribute` effect of the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This sets the HP of unit 74 (militia) to 100 (the value). Alternatively, any of the [Unit Attribute Constants](./#7-effectamount-unit-attribute "Jump to: Unit Attribute Constants") may be used to modify the corresponding unit property

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cModResource
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Modify Resource` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This adds 100 to the current food amount. Alternatively, `cAttributeSet` may be used to set the food amount to 100. Also, see the [Resource](./#9-resource "Jump to: Constant Reference > Resource")

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cEnableObject
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Enable (or disable) Object` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This disables the unit 74 (militia). Alternatively, `cAttributeEnable` may be used to enable an object instead

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cUpgradeUnit
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Upgrade Unit` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This replaces all units 74 (militia) with 75 (man at arms) on the map and also disables unit 74 and enables unit 75

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cAddAttribute
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Add Attribute` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This adds 100 (the value) to the attribute 0 (HP) of unit 74 (militia)

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cMulAttribute
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Multiply Attribute` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This multiplies the attribute 0 (HP) of unit 74 (militia) by 100 (the value)

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cMulResource
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Multiply Resource` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This multiplies the food amount by 10 (the value)

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cEnableTech
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Enable (or disable) Technology` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This enables the tech 6 (Drill). Alternatively, `cAttributeDisable` may be used to disable the tech instead

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cModifyTech
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Modify Technology` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This sets the research time of tech 22 (loom) to 10s (the value). Alternatively, any of the [Tech Attribute Constants](./#6-effectamount-technology-attribute "Jump to: Tech Attribute Constants") may be used to modify the corresponding tech property

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cSetPlayerData
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Set Player Data` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This sets the player data 0 (Civilization Name ID) to 10230 (the value)

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cSetTechCost
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Set Technology Cost` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This sets the food cost of tech 22 (loom) to 10 (the value)

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cAddTechCost
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Add Technology Cost` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This adds 10 (the) to the current food cost of tech 22 (loom)

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cDisableTech
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Disable Tech` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This disables the tech 22 (loom)

EffectAmount Effect Type.name: cModTechTime
EffectAmount Effect Type.desc: This is the ID of the `Modify Technology Time` effect for the xsEffectAmount function
